---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy | Blue Leaf Labs" description="Privacy Policy for Blue Leaf Labs.">
  <div class="wrap page-intro">
    <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  </div>
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <p><em>Last updated: October 31, 2025</em></p>
        <p>Blue Leaf Labs (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;our,&rdquo; or &ldquo;us&rdquo;) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you visit our website (<a href="https://www.blueleaflabs.org">www.blueleaflabs.org</a>). We comply with privacy laws including the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), UK GDPR, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA), and the U.S. Children&rsquo;s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We only collect personal information that you voluntarily provide:</p>
        <ul><li>First name</li><li>Last name</li><li>Email address</li></ul>
        <p>This happens when you:</p>
        <ul><li>Use our contact form</li><li>Subscribe to our newsletter</li></ul>
        <p>We do not use cookies, analytics tools, or advertising trackers.</p>
        <p>If you are under 13, please ask a parent or guardian for permission before sending any personal information.</p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information only to:</p>
        <ul><li>Respond to your messages</li><li>Send newsletters or updates (if you subscribe)</li></ul>
        <p>You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in any of our emails.</p>

        <h2>3. Parental Consent and Children&rsquo;s Privacy</h2>
        <p>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If we learn that we have collected information from a child without consent, we will delete it promptly. Parents or guardians can contact us at hello [at] blueleaflabs [dot] org to review or delete their child&rsquo;s data.</p>

        <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>For visitors in the European Economic Area (EEA) and the United Kingdom, we process information only when:</p>
        <ul><li>You have given consent (e.g., newsletter sign-up)</li><li>It&rsquo;s necessary to respond to your inquiry</li><li>It&rsquo;s required to comply with legal obligations</li></ul>
        <p>You may withdraw consent at any time by contacting us.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We keep your data only as long as needed to respond to your messages or manage your newsletter subscription, then delete it securely.</p>

        <h2>6. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your information. We may disclose data only if required by law or to protect our legal rights.</p>

        <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We use reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no online system is perfectly secure.</p>

        <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
        <ul><li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li><li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li><li>Withdraw consent for its use</li><li>Request a copy of your data (data portability)</li></ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at hello [at] blueleaflabs [dot] org.</p>

        <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>If you are located outside our country of operation, your data may be transferred and processed in another country. We ensure such transfers comply with applicable data protection laws.</p>

        <h2>10. Children&rsquo;s Privacy (COPPA Compliance)</h2>
        <p>Our website is for general educational purposes and may be visited by students, including minors. We encourage children to involve a parent or guardian when providing information online.</p>

        <h2>11. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Updates will appear on this page with a new &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date. Continued use of the site means you accept the updated policy.</p>

        <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For questions about this Privacy Policy, or if you are a parent or guardian requesting review or deletion of a child&rsquo;s information, contact us at:</p>
        <p>Blue Leaf Labs<br />Email: hello [at] blueleaflabs [dot] org<br />Website: <a href="https://www.blueleaflabs.org">www.blueleaflabs.org</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
